news.title: Kolkata: Online sanction of building plan in 15 days
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim on Saturday asked the municipal commissioner Binod Kumar to look into the matter and issue a circular in this regard.

news.title: Cash-starved Ludhiana civic body yet to revise rents on properties
news.para: ​The local bodies department, while approving the annual budget of civic body in the month of May, had asked them to re-negotiate rent agreement with tenants according to new rent control act.

news.title: Lucknow development body seeks expansion of jurisdiction
news.para: The proposal will be first presented in the board meeting of the housing and urban planning department on Monday and then to the government for approval.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's stop-work order on redevelopment worries Bhendi Bazaar residents
news.para: Construction on the first phase of the work began in 2016 and was completed in 2019, rehabilitating 610 families and 128 businesses in two towers named Al Saadah or prosperity.

news.title: West Bengal amends land policy to allot plots on freehold basis
news.para: As per the state's land allotment policy framed in 2012, land parcels could be transferred only on long-term lease for a maximum of 99 years.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents protest over 'builder floor' at Emaar Marbella
news.para: The residents pointed out that the developer had presented the project as an exclusive villa complex. However, vacant plots have been sold to individual builders, paving the way for standalone apartments within the township.

news.title: Birla Corporation to expand cement production capacity to 30 MTPA by 2030
news.para: ​The company, which has commissioned a greenfield unit at Mukutban, Maharashtra with an investment of Rs 2,744 crore, has plans to set up some new units and expand the production capacity of the existing units.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks ILD promoter to complete Gurugram project or face punitive action
news.para: ​Hearing a plea of homebuyers, RERA Chairman K K Khandelwal directed the realty company to submit a resolution plan in the next hearing on September 7 to complete the project which was launched way back in 2008-09.

news.title: Will object to Supertech move to build houses on site of twin towers: Emerald Court residents' body
news.para: The nearly 100-metre-tall twin towers -- Apex and Ceyane -- were demolished on August 28 in compliance with a landmark Supreme Court order that found their construction within Emerald Court premises in violation of norms.

news.title: Lodha Group repays offshore bonds worth $55 million ahead of scheduled maturity
news.para: The Lodha Group has repaid the bonds worth Rs 438 crore listed on the Singapore Exchange Securities Trading through its wholly owned subsidiary Lodha Developers International Ltd, Mauritius.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body officials recover property tax dues from eight owners
news.para: ​​They recovered dues from eight while one workshop was sealed and one building owner sought time till Monday.

news.title: Telangana HC stays land acquisition, move on oustees under lens
news.para: The judge made this interim order after hearing a petition filed by Cheruku Srinivas Reddy of Mutrajpally who questioned the process because it will take away his five-acre land in the village.

news.title: Base map for third master plan for Chennai yet to be prepared
news.para: The map, which will include information about the various zones, water bodies, roads, residential colonies, commercial establishments and other infrastructure, will help prepare the land-use plan and formulate strategies for the Chennai Metropolitan Area (CMA) area for the next few decades.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's operator starts collecting construction waste
news.para: The operator — Hyderabad C&D Waste Pvt Ltd — has conducted a survey and started to lift C&D waste from areas in Laxmi Nagar Zone. The NMC has provided 5 acre land to the operator for setting up the recycling plant, storage etc.

news.title: Lucknow, nearby areas to be developed as Uttar Pradesh state capital region
news.para: In a meeting with senior officials of the housing and urban planning department, Awas Vikas Parishad and all urban development authorities, the CM said that this area should include places like Unnao, Sitapur, Rae Bareli, Barabanki, Kanpur Nagar and Kanpur Dehat.
